N:bmad-idea
D:Creative Intelligence Suite (BMAD-CIS) for ideation, design thinking, innovation strategy, problem-solving, and storytelling. 5 named specialist agents — no sequential phases, all workflows available immediately.
G:bmad|cis|creative|ideation|brainstorming|design-thinking|innovation|problem-solving|storytelling|multi-agent|narrative

U[5]:
  Brainstorm ideas using 36 structured techniques across 7 categories with Carson
  Run human-centered design thinking through 5 phases with Maya
  Identify market disruption opportunities and design business models with Victor
  Diagnose complex problems with systematic root cause analysis using Dr. Quinn
  Craft compelling narratives and product stories using Sophia's 25 story frameworks

S[5]{n,action,details}:
  1,Brainstorm,Run bmad-cis-brainstorming or /cis-brainstorm → Carson facilitates using 36 ideation techniques → brainstorming session output
  2,Design,Run bmad-cis-design-thinking or /cis-design-thinking → Maya guides 5-phase process → design thinking report with prototypes and test plan
  3,Innovate,Run bmad-cis-innovation-strategy or /cis-innovation-strategy → Victor applies JTBD/Blue Ocean/BMC → innovation strategy with roadmap
  4,Solve,Run bmad-cis-problem-solving or /cis-problem-solving → Dr. Quinn applies TRIZ/TOC/5-Whys → root cause analysis + solution plan
  5,Narrate,Run bmad-cis-storytelling or /cis-storytelling → Sophia selects from 25 frameworks → complete narrative with emotional arc

R[3]:
  All workflows are anytime — no sequential phases. Use any command independently in any order.
  Agent loading commands (/cis-agent-*) start a direct conversation without running the full workflow.
  Sophia (storyteller) uses sidecar memory — she remembers story preferences and history across sessions.
